data-triple-N3.o: "Pope of the Roman Catholic Church from 1939 to 1958"@en

"Pius XII, born Eugenio Maria Giuseppe Giovanni Pacelli (2 March 1876 9 October 1958), reigned as Pope, head of the Catholic Church and sovereign of Vatican City State, from 2 March 1939 until his death in 1958. He is the most recent Pope to date to take the name "Pius" upon being elected as Pope."@en
